rComments: I think she cares about her students but her organization makes it so that even she herself seems confused about what she is doing. She will tell you not to do something and then mark you down for not doing that exact thing. She makes numerous mistakes while grading so always double-check her comments are logical. Participation marks help

She treats all her students like they are in middle-school. A lot of homework are free points and you're going to need all of them. She grades all the big evaluations depending on her mood and if you don't suck up to her, you will get a bad grade since she thinks she knows everything (very very strict grader and doesn't follow her grading criteria)

You can tell that she was trying to keep at heart the students mental health but her brightspace is very unorganized which makes it hard to find specific intructions. Also, her projects are simple yet hard to follow due to lack of instructions. She grades french harder than my french prof.

This class had the potential to be really informative but the lack of organization on BrightSpace made it hard to keep track of anything. 40% of the grade is pretty much participation which is nice but in the written work, she cares more about the quality of french than content. I did like that she made interactive Wooclaps to keep us intrigued!

Can't take your eyes off this class for even a minute. 4 to 5 tasks are due weekly. Although you get a lot free bonus, but each of them weights less than 1 %. So by the end of this course, I feel it sucked my soul out, totally unbelievable. The group assignment and final essay worth a big time but toughly graded. Needs triple brain power and time.

Expect to be teaching yourself the entire course. She hosts one class a week and spends most of it off-topic and the things she does discuss are too brief to be useful for the final essay and midterm project. Her bright space is chaotic and overwhelming. Most of her assessments are pointless. It's not a hard class but she makes it an annoying one.

Teacher is not as bad as people are saying but for online the class was extremely unorganized and it took a while to get to understand it but once you do its not very hard. If you get lucky with a good group the class should not be bad since there are many group projects. Not a bad class but would not recommend if you dont need it.

By far my worst class this semester. Brightspace was very messy and confusing. Too much group work for a virtual class. Grading and expectations were very unclear. Students complained about the work load so she said she'd reduce it. She increased it instead! Don't take this class
She cares and has good ideas but her brightspace is too confusing.

You can tell the prof tries and cares about students but organizations is not her strong suit. All year I was lost with her set up on brightspace.... I would not recommend taking this class if its given online. It definitely adds stress to your semester. I did however like the fact we had group projects and a lot of bonus points !

You can tell she tries hard for her students. But she does not give enough instructions. Her instructions are hidden in brightspace. I have never seen a messier brightspace omg!! I don't recommend taking a class with her, especially if its online and if its not mandatory for your program
Super disorganized and hard to follow. She was hard to contact and assigned way to many group projects considering the current pandemic. Just don't.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Group projects', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: Brightspace so messy. I still probably haven't looked at 1/4 of it. Lorie believed that meant she could give more work and every week we had 6hours+ of readings, videos and material to do. Very unmotivating. She expects everything to link to the class, especially the cover letter praising it.. I would never hire someone with this letter. Just no.
teacherRatingTags: ['Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Just dont. Group projects. Little to no feedback. Does not want the best for her students. Confusing. She removed her email from the syllabus because too many students were contacting her confused. Her rubrics and explanations for the projects do not match and have opposite criteria. Does not correct these errors.

Took this class to learn more about social work but now I want nothing to do with it. The class itself is easy, but this prof makes it tiring. She posts new content almost every day; brightspace was always flooded with notifs from this class. Group projects, weekly quizzes, assignments, discussions. It was the most stressful class I've ever had.

As an online course, its disorganized. Class content is all over the place and I was always worried about missing something. Too many weekly components (quiz, reflection, discussion posts..). The discussion forum is a joke by making you post 2-3x a week to get full marks. Also I don't like all the group work given that its a virtual class

Rediculous professor, very easy class. About half your final grade is composed of participation exercises that you get full points if you complete so if you wanna A it's just a matter of doing them. However, she might be one of the worst professors at uottawa. Feels like you're in a high school class, she simply isn't meant to teach university.

Donne des quiz sur des sujets personnelles tels que notre identité social et orientation sexuelle. De plus, notre passé et c'est pas acceptable de demander se genre de questions sur notre vie personelle. Elle est vraiment la pire prof que j'ai jamais eux, pas de respect pour ses élèves. Vraiment pas correcte de demander tes questions personnels.

So many quizzes. Nothing learned in lectures, she only talks about her personal life and nothing about social services. If you want to pass, make sure to read. To pass the quizzes, search up the questions online and you will find all the answers. Soooo boring and monotone, only reads her slides, does not know what she is saying half the time.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Bad teacher. Very boring and if you'd like to learn about her personal life it is a good course for you, she will always talk about her kids Simon and Nicolas. We are not even learning what's a social worker, were just learning about health. Not recommended as a teacher. The midterm is not clear and the questions are repeating themselves.

in general she is not bad but, I did not like her approach with the students. I had the impression that she took us for children. She often wandered about in her class, and I wanted to get out of her class several times before the end because she was repeating herself a lot. The demands of the work was really higher than the material seen in class
teacherRatingTags: ['EXTRA CREDIT', 'Get ready to read', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: She is a nice person, but I would never take a class with her ever again. There were no exams in that class, only papers and pop quizzes. She is a really tough grader and when you ask her a question, her reply doesnt even answer the question. Trust me dont take her class! Too much work, and an A is almost impossible.
Elle ce croit, ce perd dans ses sujets, le cours est très long, quiz et présence surprise. En plus d'assister à tout les cours par peur de manquer un quiz surprise les quiz sont tricky.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Take home exam which is great. She is super caring and wants us to do well. I learnt a lot about myself in this course. Would recommend this prof. to anyone. She does a good job at conveying the subject matter. It is easy to do well in this course so long as you try. Has 4 pop quizzes worth 5% each which was kind of tough. Other than that good tho.

All in all, Lorie is a good prof. She explains her slides very well and shares them with the class. She is always there to answer questions and gives a good idea of what will be on the exams. 10% extra credit is given by participation in kahoots. However she gives a lot of readings and has pop quizzes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'EXTRA CREDIT', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: She's an amazing first year prof, super passionate and caring! Her lectures are always organized and interesting. She really looks out for her students and their success. The class was always engaging with guest speakers and Kahoot quizzes. The two exams were very well based on the course material as well.

For a first year class, she taught it very well. The subjects were very well explained, she had guests from the community to teach a specific subject (which made the class interesting) and she is a very understandable person. Overall, she is made to teach first years.

Le cours est très pertinent parce qu'il discute des réalités tabous dans notre société. Le prof nous démontre ça avec beaucoup de patience et passion. Je conseille ce cours aux gens qui aiment beaucoup écrire, lire et apprendre en profondeur sur les enjeux véritables de la société. Néanmoins, l'effort est nécessaire pour passer le cours.

This teacher is one of the best teachers I've had at University. From the first day, all assignments are given and needed to be handed at the end of the semester which gives you the chance to do your own schedule. Lots of lectures but very easy credit, she also gives out many chances to get bonuses.

One of my worst prof yet. Doesn't teach well, really boring lectures, a lot of projects and homework to do and she doesn't clear up things when you don't understand and her exams are hard and makes no sense. Avoid if u can.

In all honesty, the teacher is not that bad, the problem is the fact that she gave us about 24 assignments. So if you like writing, go right ahead. The subject itself is interesting though, just not the class. she's always late, so if you're always on time it's annoying.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Perfect! She's really good.

Although I enjoyed the subject the way it was organized was sub par. Too many things posted, can't find assignment info without searching forever for it. You learn more from videos than from her actual lecturing. Changes assignments with no warning. Takehome was an 8 page essay given 4days to complete. Underwhelmed, frustrated and disattified. 1/10
